114. ciuem Atticam. The Lemnian mother must have been of genuine Athenian extraction: otherwise Phanium could. only have been made legitimate by a vote of the citizens or by proclamation at the meeting of the plu-amnes. The penalty for a false claim of citizenship was very heavy. See Donaldson, ‘Women in Greece’, Contemp. Review, March, 1879.

115. bonam bonis, combining the ideas of good birth and good. morals. In most of Ter. ’s plays the obscure heroine turns out to be an Athenian citizen. Cf. Les F. 116. Solon punished the procurer in case of the seduction of a free woman with death: the seducet with a fine of 20 drachmas See Grote, Hist. of Greece, 011 Solon [quoted in Aeschines (Timarch.) pp. 16—78].

Fourb. de S. Act 3, sc. 12 ‘une inconnue sans naissance et sans bien’.]
